route 288 , the circumferential highway run around the south - western quadrant of the richmond new urban region , open in late 2004 .
already it be change development pattern for the worse and cause localize traffic congestion around its exit .
the richmond time - dispatch tell the tale today about the impact on the huguenot trail in powhatan county .
traffic have more than double in one section of huguenot trail since 288 open , report will jones .
speed and accident have surge as well :
17 accident have be report near the intersection of winterfield road so far this year , up from 12 for all of 2004 .
dale totten , resident engineer for the virginia department of transportation , note that vdot would four - lane the road for about $ 13 million if it have more money .
of course , vdot have no more money for road construction in the richmond region .
one reason be that vdot , at the behest of local politician and booster , spent all its friggin ' money on 288 !
where 's homer simpson when you need him ?
this be a major `` d'oh ! '' moment .
as we predict , route 288 be generate residential development in scarcely populate area all around its exit , overtax the local country road .
while the limit access highway might provide limit traffic relief for people drive back and forth between chesterfield and goochland county , other people be make choice about where they live and work ,
and they be create traffic congestion in new place .
the only thing that surprise me be how rapidly this be happen .
even i think there might be a lag of three or four year .
if route 288 have already create a $ 13 million road - construction in just this one exist , think of the liability it have create for all of its exit !
here 's another prodiction :
after a few more year of scatter subdivision development and approval of mega @-@ commercial project at major 288 intersection , the need for new road improvement will soar .
before the end of the decade , we may well see the unfunded liability zoom well past the original $ 400 million it take to build the original highway .
