afghanistan ( af )
narcotic
head of the u.n. drug office antonio maria costa say that afghanistan have produce so much opium in recent year that the taliban be cut back poppy cultivation and stockpile raw opium in an effort to support price and preserve a major source of finance for the insurgency .
head of the u.n. drug office antonio maria costa say that afghanistan have produce so much opium in recent year that the taliban be cut back poppy cultivation and stockpile raw opium in an effort to support price and preserve a major source of finance for the insurgency .
costa say this to reporter last week as the u.n. drug office office prepare to release its latest survey of afghanistan 's opium crop .
the survey show that poppy cultivation have retreat in much of afghanistan and be overwhelmingly concentrate in 7 of 34 province where the insurgency remain strong , most of those in the south .
the survey be issue november 27 , 2008 .
the unite nation find that the result be a 19 percent reduction in the amount of land devoted to opium in afghanistan even though the total tonnage of opium produce drop by just 6 percent .
the study state that the high output per acre be attributed to a good grow season in the south .
the southern region be a heavily irrigate area where the taliban maintain a strong presence in 5 province and have systematically encourage opium cultivation as a way to finance their insurgency for several year .
the u.n. estimate the insurgent make as much as 300 million dollar from the opium trade last year .
costa say a lot of war effort can be fund with 2 to 300 million dollar .
the taliban have produce an amount of opium that far exceed world demand due to 3 successive year of bumper crop .
costa say the result be a glut that be depress the price , which drop by approximately 20 percent .
costa say that the fact that price have not collapse already be evidence that the taliban , drug lord and even some farmer have stockpile the opium .
an increase amount be also be process in afghanistan .
costa add that insurgent have be hold significant amount of opium .
costa say the surplus be as much as 11000 ton , or more than twice world demand in the last 3 year and threaten to devalue their stockpile .
the unite nation find that afghanistan produce 8500 ton of opium in 2008 .
world demand be estimate at about 4400 ton per year .
the taliban this year be take a passive stance toward cultivation and put less pressure on afghan farmer to plant opium poppy .
this then support the current price .
costa be an italian diplomat who have serve at the u.n. office on drug and crime for 6 year .
