south africa ( za )
international ; terrorism ; government ; money
the south african government impose a ban that prohibit the recruitment of people inside or outside of south africa for mercenary or foreign military assistance .
on 011006 the citizen newspaper state that it be illegal for south africans to be involve in mercenary activity or to render foreign military assistance inside or outside of south africa .
the citizen newspaper state that the south african foreign ministry announce on 011005 that the south african government impose the mercenary activity ban follow report that 1000 muslims with military train have enlist to leave south africa for afghanistan to fight for the taliban against the unite state .
a report claim that muslims against illegitimate leader have claim that the 1000 muslim men with military train have volunteer their service and have receive the back of local businessmen .
report claim that all of the 1000 muslim men with military train be over the age of 18 .
muslims against illegitimate leader be a cape town @-@ based group .
the report be refute by the muslim judicial council .
south africa 's foreign ministry state that south africa 's foreign military assistance act prohibit the recruitment of people inside or outside of south africa for mercenary or foreign military assistance .
south africa 's foreign military assistance act mean that no person be allow to offer military assistance to any state , organ of state , group or other country , unless permission be grant by the national conventional arm control committee .
south africa 's foreign military assistance act mean that foreign military assistance could be render only in accordance with an agreement approve by the national conventional arm control committee .
the south african foreign ministry state that any person find in violation of south africa 's foreign military assistance act or any person that fail to receive permission to participate in foreign military activity could be prosecute and sentence to a fine , imprisonment or both .
