peru ( pe )
international ; money ; crime ; human right ; government ; narcotic ; politics ; leader
former peruvian spy chief vladimiro montesinos convict of illegally take control of the national intelligence service during ex @-@ president fujimori 's tenure .
montesinos have be sentence to 9 year and 4 month for the conviction .
montesinos plan to appeal the sentence .
on 1 july 2002 former peruvian spy chief during the government of ex @-@ president alberto fujimori , vladimiro montesinos , be convict of illegally take control of the national intelligence service when montesinos be suppose to be only an adviser to the spy agency .
montesinos be sentence to 9 year and 4 month in prison for abuse of authority .
the sentence also order montesinos pay a fine of 3 million dollar as compensation to the state .
anti @-@ corruption judge saul pena state montesinos have admit to the abuse of authority charge .
this be the first rule of more than 50 charge against montesinos which include corruption , drug traffic , illegal arm deal and human right violation .
montesinos be allege to run a network of bribe .
a leak videotape show montesinos bribe a congressman to switch to the government party and trigger event that culminated in fujimori 's resignation in november 2000 .
fujimori be accuse of dereliction of duty and embezzlement and have be in self @-@ impose exile in japan since resign to avoid the legal action from the peruvian authority under the protection of dual nationality .
montesinos flee peru in october 2000 but be capture in venezuela on 23 june 2001 .
montesinos hear the sentence at the callao naval base where montesinos have be imprison since 2001 .
montesinos state montesinos would consult with a defense lawyer to appeal .
