hong kong ( hk ) ; china ( cn )
technology ; international
hong kong university collaborate with university , business and government sector of mainland china to coordinate train programs and research centers to promote high @-@ tech research , commercialization , and technology transfer .
in 2004 hong kong tertiary institute actively contribute to improve relation between hong kong and mainland china in the research and development of high technology .
hong kong university have collaborate with tertiary education , business and government sector of mainland china to direct train programs and research centers to promote research commercialization and technology transfer .
in june 2004 hong kong polytechnic university ( polyu ) join national university science and technology park of the virtual university park in shenzhen , china become the first tertiary institution of hong kong to establish research centers and train facility in mainland china .
president of polyu poon chung @-@ kwong state that both public and private sector in hong kong be strengthen connection with mainland china in various area .
poon state that cooperation between hong kong and mainland china will facilitate university to more effectively promote technology transfer and human resource development in the mainland create positive result for both hong kong and china .
city university of hong kong ( cityu ) and the university of science and technology of china ( ustc ) in anhui province sign an agreement in june to jointly establish a high level joint research center in suzhou .
the university of science and technology of china be a university establish by the chinese academy of science ( cas ) .
the agreement be based on the principle of mutually beneficial collaboration in which both university complement each other 's strength in work together on joint research project , supervision and teach of research student and in administer professional train opportunity .
in addition to partner with education institute hong kong university have also join large @-@ scale high technology exchange programs in mainland china in order to enhance communication between the mainland and hong kong in the discipline .
the hong kong university of science and technology ( hkust ) demonstrate its latest achievement in research and development at the 6 th annual china hi @-@ tech fair ( chtf ) hold in shenzhen in october 2004 .
hkust demonstrate more than 30 new technology and product cover a wide range of technology include nanotechnology , multimedia , logistics and rfid technology , advance manufacture , and biotechnology .
hkust also collaborate with a prominent mainland manufacturer on the development of a nanomaterial @-@ based high @-@ capacity lithium battery .
this collaboration be the most recent in a series of successful technology transfer agreement reach by hkust .
hkust president paul ching @-@ wu chu state --
hkust be increase fund to research new technology require by industry in the pearl river delta .
the university will continue to leverage its extensive relationship with international research institution and multi @-@ national corporation to enhance the development of advanced technology which can find immediate practical application in china .
